</target_code>
<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:The initial assignments to timeout.tv_sec = 0 and timeout.tv_usec = 0 at the start of MHD_select are executed unconditionally but are either overwritten later (when tv is set to &timeout) or never used (when tv is set to NULL). Removing those initial assignments would not change program behaviour, so they constitute dead code under MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>
